                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>P<hi rend=\"sup\">to</hi>\n                                                  Cabello</placeName>\n                                        <date>24 January 1854</date>.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr.</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Dear Sir!</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">By <persName>Captain Wilkins</persName> of the\n                                        Paer, I wrote<lb/> you, forwarding at the same time Nine\n                                        Spanish dollars<lb/> and by the Venezuela, <persName>Capt<hi\n                                                  rend=\"sup\">n</hi> Wilson</persName>, who arrived\n                                        after<lb/>wards, I received the Hebrew Grammar and\n                                        Lexicon,<lb/> as also your favor of the <date>24<hi\n                                                  rend=\"sup\">th</hi> of October</date> last; I now\n                                        beg<lb/> to remind you of the two copies of the new\n                                        translation of<lb/> the Bible, and one copy of the form of\n                                        prayers, as speci<lb/>fied on the prospectus forwarded by\n                                        letter of the <date>5<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> of De<lb/>cember\n                                                  1852</date>, as I observe in the last numbers of\n                                        the<lb/> Occident, that they are near being issued, if not\n                                        issued<lb/> already.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Enclosed I beg to hand you a list of some\n                                        works<lb/> etc. which I would wish very much to possess,\n                                        especial<lb/>ly for the use of my children, as my family\n                                        will shortly<lb/> come to reside in this place, where\n                                        educational works<lb/> are scarce to be had, of inferior\n                                        utility and at exorbi<lb/>tant prices. I thought you would\n                                        forgive the liberty<lb/> I take in begging the favor of you\n                                        to procure them for<lb/> me, as I felt assured of your\n                                        willingness to be of service<lb/> to a fellow-creature, and\n                                        perform a good act; but as I<lb/> am also very far from\n                                        wishing, that you should any<lb/>\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">ways</hi></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3vh5d412/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
